Members of Reaction Unit South Africa said a device
resembling a bomb was found inside the Imam Hussein Mosque in Durban Kwazulu-Natal. Imam Hussein Mosque is the same place that was attacked
last week, leaving one person was killed. RUSA said the area has been evacuated and the SAPS Bomb
Disposal Unit has been summoned. The device connected to a Nokia mobile phone was found under the Moulanas chair. It was moved by a worshiper. "The home of the victim that died after he had his
throat slit has also been evacuated. "The device found is a small cellphone connected via
wires to a white capsule," said Rusa spokesperson Prem Balram.  